java.lang.reflect

Class WeakCache<K,P,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.reflect.WeakCache<K,P,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - type of keys
    P - type of parameters
    V - type of values

    final class WeakCache<K,P,V>
extends Object
    Cache mapping pairs of (key, sub-key) -> value. Keys and values are weakly but sub-keys are strongly referenced. Keys are passed directly to get(K, P) method which also takes a parameter. Sub-keys are calculated from keys and parameters using the subKeyFactory function passed to the constructor. Values are calculated from keys and parameters using the valueFactory function passed to the constructor. Keys can be null and are compared by identity while sub-keys returned by subKeyFactory or values returned by valueFactory can not be null. Sub-keys are compared using their Object.equals(java.lang.Object) method. Entries are expunged from cache lazily on each invocation to get(K, P), containsValue(V) or size() methods when the WeakReferences to keys are cleared. Cleared WeakReferences to individual values don't cause expunging, but such entries are logically treated as non-existent and trigger re-evaluation of valueFactory on request for their key/subKey.
    Author:
    Peter Levart

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public V get(K key,
    P parameter)
        Look-up the value through the cache. This always evaluates the subKeyFactory function and optionally evaluates valueFactory function if there is no entry in the cache for given pair of (key, subKey) or the entry has already been cleared.
        Parameters:
        key - possibly null key
        parameter - parameter used together with key to create sub-key and value (should not be null)
        Returns:
        the cached value (never null)
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if parameter passed in or sub-key calculated by subKeyFactory or value calculated by valueFactory is null.

        public boolean containsValue(V value)

        Parameters:
        value - the non-null value to check
        Returns:
        true if given value is already cached
